  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 2.34,
      "text": "So, what actually changed with clothes?"
    },
    {
      "start": 2.94,
      "end": 4.76,
      "text": "It wasn't just that fabric got cheaper."
    },
    {
      "start": 6.8,
      "end": 9.12,
      "text": "It was a paradigm shift in manufacturing"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.84,
      "end": 13.34,
      "text": "from crafting individual objects to designing molds."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.64,
      "end": 18.18,
      "text": "Make the mold once, produce unlimited identical parts,"
    },
    {
      "start": 18.7,
      "end": 22.56,
      "text": "refine the mold once, every future part improves automatically."
    },
    {
      "start": 23.94,
      "end": 28.28,
      "text": "And when there's a defect, you don't patch individual parts."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.84,
      "end": 33.32,
      "text": "You fix the mold, and that fix applies to every part you'll ever make again."
    },
    {
      "start": 34.78,
      "end": 38.28,
      "text": "This is the real shift, not cheaper material,"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.9,
      "end": 40.84,
      "text": "a migration of where value lives."
    },
    {
      "start": 41.14,
      "end": 44.12,
      "text": "In crafting, value lives in the object."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.72,
      "end": 48.3,
      "text": "You protect the object, losing the chair is losing everything."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.88,
      "end": 52.88,
      "text": "In molding, value lives in the specification."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.38,
      "end": 55.1,
      "text": "The mold, the plastic part,"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.9,
      "end": 58.26,
      "text": "disposable, regenerated at will."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.6,
      "end": 61.92,
      "text": "This is prompt-driven development."
    },
    {
      "start": 62.94,
      "end": 66.68,
      "text": "The prompt is your mold, the code is just plastic."
    }
  ]
}